    <string name="custom_rules_help">Custom Rules Help</string>
    <string name="custom_rules_help_text">Custom rules are applied before filter lists, giving them higher priority.\n\nSupported formats:\n• Block domain: ||example.com^ or example.com\n• Block wildcard: ||*.ads.example.com^ or *.ads.example.com\n• Allow domain: @@||example.com^\n• Allow wildcard: @@||*.example.com^\n• Comment: ! This is a comment\n\nExamples:\n• ||ads.example.com^ - Blocks ads.example.com and all subdomains\n• ||*.tracker.com^ - Blocks any subdomain of tracker.com (but not tracker.com itself)\n• @@||example.com^ - Allows example.com (overrides blocklists)\n• *.ads.example.com - Blocks x.ads.example.com, y.ads.example.com, etc.\n• ! My custom rules - A comment line</string>
